rotocol/actions.ActionC2CConnect`.","Current contract code/tests use `groundseg/protocol/contracts/...` (`goseg/protocol/contracts/catalog/action/specs.go`, `goseg/uploadsvc/actions_test.go`, `goseg/protocol/contracts/conformance/fixtures_test.go`), indicating documentation-to-runtime contract drift."],"impact_scope":"subsystem","fix_scope":"single_edit","confidence":"high"},"initialization_coupling":{"evidence":["`goseg/config/bootstrap.go` relies on package-global mutable state (`globalConfig`, `Ready`, `GSContainers`, `initOnce`), making behavior dependent on prior process init sequence.","`goseg/importer/importer.go` stores request-critical runtime state in globals (`uploadSessions`, `uploadDir`, `tempDir`) initialized out-of-band by `Initialize`.","`goseg/broadcast/state.go` and `goseg/docker/events/events.go` both maintain mutable process-wide default runtimes via `SetDefault...`/`ResetDefault...`, coupling test/runtime order across packages."],"impact_scope":"codebase","fix_scope":"architectural_change","confidence":"high"},"convention_outlier":{"evidence":["Most reviewed packages use lowercase-wrapped error text, but `goseg/shipworkflow/newship_service.go` emits capitalized messages (`\"Couldn't ...\"`, `\"Unknown NewShip action\"`) that diverge from prevailing error style.","The same subsystem uses both acronym styles (`WiFi` vs `Wifi`) across adjacent files (`goseg/system/wifi_runtime_api.go`, `goseg/system/wifi_runtime_methods.go`)."],"impact_scope":"module","fix_scope":"multi_file_refactor","confidence":"high","issues_preventing_higher_score":"Style and naming conventions are mostly consistent globally, but there are localized style islands in wifi/newship flows."},"api_surface_coherence":{"evidence":["`goseg/docker/orchestration/container_config.go` exposes both typed (`ContainerConfigForType`) and string-cast (`ContainerConfigForTypeString`) entrypoints for the same API, creating dual call patterns.","`goseg/shipworkflow/operations_runtime.go` keeps typed generic helpers (`persistShipUrbitSectionConfig[T]`) but still routes through untyped `func(any) error` seams, indicating partially coherent API boundaries."],"impact_scope":"subsystem","fix_scope":"multi_file_refactor","confidence":"high","issues_preventing_higher_score":"API direction is generally improving toward typed seams, but legacy untyped/string adapters remain on public paths."},"authorization_consistency":{"evidence":["`goseg/importer/importer.go` enforces upload authorization with token headers plus `ValidateUploadSessionTokenFn` checks in `validateUploadRequest` and `setUploadSessionWithRuntime`.","`goseg/shipworkflow/newship_service.go` exported action handlers (`HandleNewShip`, `HandleNewShipBoot`, `CancelNewShip`) execute provisioning/deletion paths without an explicit auth context or token parameter at this boundary."],"impact_scope":"subsystem","fix_scope":"multi_file_refactor","confidence":"medium"}},"findings":[{"dimension":"initialization_coupling","identifier":"global_runtime_singletons_order_dependent","summary":"Core services rely on mutable package-level singletons and init order, creating hidden boot/test coupling.","related_files":["goseg/config/bootstrap.go","goseg/importer/importer.go","goseg/broadcast/state.go","goseg/docker/events/events.go"],"evidence":["Config/bootstrap gates state through `initOnce` plus globals (`Ready`, `globalConfig`, `GSContainers`).","Importer request path depends on global `uploadDir`/`tempDir`/`uploadSessions` populated by prior `Initialize` call.","Broadcast/events each expose mutable default runtimes via `SetDefault...`, so behavior can vary by prior caller mutation."],"suggestion":"Introduce explicit application-scoped runtime structs (config state, importer session store, event broker, broadcast state) and pass them through startup wiring; keep package defaults only as thin compatibility adapters.","confidence":"high","impact_scope":"codebase","fix_scope":"architectural_change","root_cause_cluster":"mutable_process_singleton_pattern"},{"dimension":"type_safety","identifier":"urbit_section_mutation_uses_any","summary":"Urbit section update seams erase compile-time types with `any`, allowing invalid mutator/section pairings until runtime.","related_files":["goseg/docker/orchestration/runtime_ops.go","goseg/shipworkflow/operations_runtime.go"],"evidence":["Runtime contract declares `UpdateUrbitSectionFn func(patp string, section UrbitConfigSection, mutateFn func(any) error) error`.","`persistShipUrbitSection` forwards a `func(any) error`, so section-target compatibility is not enforced by the type system."],"suggestion":"Replace the untyped section mutator seam with typed per-section callbacks (or a generic typed registry keyed by section enum) so invalid section/mutator combinations fail at compile time.","confidence":"high","impact_scope":"subsystem","fix_scope":"multi_file_refactor","root_cause_cluster":"legacy_untyped_runtime_seams"},{"dimension":"contract_coherence","identifier":"readme_contract_entrypoint_drift","summary":"README contract guidance points to deprecated/incorrect action package paths, diverging from actual runtime contract modules.","related_files":["README.md","goseg/protocol/contracts/catalog/action/specs.go","goseg/uploadsvc/actions_test.go"],"evidence":["README says canonical websocket action registry is `protocol/actions` and references `groundseg/protocol/actions.ActionC2CConnect`.","Current implementation/tests consume `groundseg/protocol/contracts` action bindings and catalog specs."],"suggestion":"Update README contract section to the current `protocol/contracts` entrypoints and keep referenced constant paths synchronized with conformance tests.","confidence":"high","impact_scope":"subsystem","fix_scope":"single_edit"},{"dimension":"naming_quality","identifier":"wifi_acronym_casing_drift","summary":"Wi-Fi runtime naming alternates between `WiFi` and `Wifi`, reducing discoverability and grepability within one API family.","related_files":["goseg/system/wifi_runtime_api.go","goseg/system/wifi_runtime_methods.go"],"evidence":["API file exports `WiFiRuntimeService`, `IsWiFiEnabled`, `StartWiFiInfoLoop`.","Runtime methods file defines fields like `NewWifiClient`/`WifiInfoTicker` and `wifiNmcli*` types, mixing acronym style in the same subsystem."],"suggestion":"Normalize acronym casing to one convention (`WiFi` or `Wifi`) across the wifi runtime/service surface and update dependent call sites/tests together.","confidence":"high","impact_scope":"module","fix_scope":"multi_file_refactor","root_cause_cluster":"naming_convention_drift"},{"dimension":"authorization_consistency","identifier":"newship_boundary_missing_explicit_auth_context","summary":"High-impact new-ship operations expose handler APIs without explicit authorization context while upload flows enforce token checks at boundary.","related_files":["goseg/shipworkflow/newship_service.go","goseg/importer/importer.go"],"evidence":["`validateUploadRequest` and session setup in importer require upload token IDs/hashes and authorization results.","`HandleNewShip` / `HandleNewShipBoot` / `CancelNewShip` accept payload/action input and trigger provisioning/deletion paths without auth token/session parameters at this API boundary."],"suggestion":"Align boundary contracts by requiring an authenticated actor/session context for new-ship entrypoints (or enforce an explicit pre-authorized command type) and document that contract next to handler APIs.","confidence":"medium","impact_scope":"subsystem","fix_scope":"multi_file_refactor","root_cause_cluster":"inconsistent_boundary_auth_contracts"}],"retrospective":{"root_causes":["Long-lived package-level singleton state remains the default integration mechanism across core subsystems.","Type-hardening is partial: typed wrappers exist, but legacy untyped seams (`any` and string adapters) still define key boundaries.","Documentation governance has not fully tracked protocol package migration."],"likely_symptoms":[